      "name": "Absolute hemolysis index comparison against FDA pump experimental data",
      "description": "CFD-predicted normalised index of haemolysis (NIH) values compared against five experimental operating points from the FDA benchmark dataset. Mean absolute error 0.0041 g/100 L across all operating points. Monte Carlo propagation (n=2000) yields 95th-percentile NIH below clinical threshold at all points.",
