    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team determined that the CFD hemolysis model meets the minimum threshold for regulatory submission under the agreed risk-benefit framework. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification confirms 95th-percentile NIH predictions remain below the clinical threshold across all five COU operating points. The central credibility claim (https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-hemolysis-credibility-claim) consolidates the technical basis. Seven of thirteen credibility factors were formally assessed; all show achieved levels below required levels, consistent with a Low assurance level. Six factors remain epistemic gaps. The submission is accepted with the understanding that identified gaps will be addressed in the next assessment cycle prior to pivotal study initiation.",
